Maputo and Pretoria enjoy strong and long-standing bilateral ties. JOHANNESBURG - All eyes will be on Cape Town as the State of the Nation Address (Sona) is set to take centre in the mother city on Thursday [20 June]. Various roads will be closed leading up to the first Sona of the 6th parliament and motorists are urged to take alternative routes to avoid traffic congestion. Below is a list of the roads that will be closed: Roads to be closed for rehearsals on 18-19 June 2019 17:00 to 23:59 Road Closures on 20 June 2019 06:00 to 23:45 (Temporary) 17:45 to 19:30 17:00 to 20:00 18:00 to 19:30